our inner voice what is it is our inner voice just our thoughts or is it much more than that when we meditate or pray does it seem like our inner voice comes from god some people declare that we have in ourselves an inner master who from our innermost background sometimes called our heart expresses a vigilant attention towards our behavior keeps an eye on our life and in the form of voice suggests further behavior what to do in case of doubt what to do in case of danger how to express our most precious hopes all this may be perceived by us as direct or quite often as parallel suggestions where we also may get guidance about what we may decide when a choice seems to be necessary between two or more possible courses of action we may imagine our inner master our inner voice the way we want the way we are acquainted to the way of our tradition we may feel that it is a voice camuflated in our thoughts or we may believe that it is much more than that when we experience an inspirational revelation when we in our own inner way for instance thru meditation and or even thru uttered prayer consider things and hope for things and in solutions regarding aspects of our existence then we may feel that it is being done from or by the inner voice a holy voice even the utmost holy voice that might be coming from the absolute and that is what is certainly right and corroborative for us we might not necessarily have to try to find out of the precise wherecome of that voice we might just listen attentively to its content and upon that we might deduce a guidance or construct a guidance for our further behavior Ten Commandments Yoga Sutras of Patanjali Religious Society of Friends Past teachings of Prem Rawat Consciousness God Prayer Criticisms of Charismatic and Pentecostal belief The nature of God in Western theology Simone Weil Goodness and value theory Religion Meditation Subud Sabbath Book of Isaiah Christian eschatology Prayer in Christianity Sikhism primary beliefs and principles T